01:38:53,953 --> 01:38:56,046
你也是他們的一分子?
Does that make you one of them?

940
01:39:08,000 --> 01:39:10,127
別逼我用這個
Don't make me use this.

941
01:39:25,151 --> 01:39:26,709
起風了
Wind's come up.

942
01:39:27,053 --> 01:39:28,315
越來越冷了
It's getting colder too.

943
01:39:29,222 --> 01:39:31,656
另一場暴風就要來了
Must be another storm.

944
01:39:35,328 --> 01:39:36,761
還要什麼?
Anything else?

945
01:39:38,464 --> 01:39:40,432
我不是說要你....
l didn't mean for you to....

946
01:39:40,633 --> 01:39:44,228
你再不下床走動你的腿就要爛掉
Your legs are going to rot off if you don't try to walk.

947
01:39:44,604 --> 01:39:46,333
-我受傷了 -你懶惰!
-l'm hurt. -You're lazy!

948
01:39:46,539 --> 01:39:47,699
懶惰?
Lazy?

949
01:39:47,974 --> 01:39:50,204
我的胃上穿了一個洞...
l got a hole in my stomach...

950
01:39:50,409 --> 01:39:51,933
...而且我很虛弱
...and l'm weak.

951
01:39:52,144 --> 01:39:55,739
這周圍只有雪和草...
The  big meals around here are snow and grass...

952
01:39:55,948 --> 01:39:58,007
...而且我們的草就要用完了
...and we're running out of grass.

953
01:40:08,060 --> 01:40:09,357
你要幹什麼?
What're you doing?

954
01:40:36,622 --> 01:40:37,816
把早餐給我吧!
Give me a break!

955
01:40:40,359 --> 01:40:41,656
我去檢查一下關口
l'm going to check the pass.

956
01:40:43,563 --> 01:40:45,190
你為什麼這麼著急?
Why are you in such a hurry?

957
01:40:45,398 --> 01:40:47,696
我們可以考慮一下更糟的地方
l could think of worse places.

958
01:40:48,701 --> 01:40:50,896
或者更糟的軍隊
Or l could think of worse company.

959
01:40:58,277 --> 01:40:59,608
好極了!
Perfect!

960
01:41:57,737 --> 01:41:58,829
救命!
Help!

961
01:42:06,512 --> 01:42:07,308
救命!
Help!

962
01:42:11,050 --> 01:42:12,142
救命!
Please!

963
01:42:13,552 --> 01:42:14,519
快來呀!
Quick!

964
01:42:25,665 --> 01:42:27,257
上帝呀, 救救我!
God, help me!

965
01:42:47,119 --> 01:42:49,110
我告訴你了我沒事
l told you that's all there was.

966
01:42:50,389 --> 01:42:52,448
正因為如此你該吃了它
That's why you should have it.

967
01:42:57,863 --> 01:42:59,694
我知道你能走
l knew you could walk.

968
01:43:02,134 --> 01:43:03,362
你真奇怪
You're weird.

969
01:43:04,270 --> 01:43:05,168
你知道嗎？?
lKnow that?

970
01:43:28,828 --> 01:43:31,194
我曾經在月亮上走過, Abby
We walked on the moon once, Abby.

971
01:43:32,064 --> 01:43:33,497
真的?
So?

972
01:43:34,100 --> 01:43:36,068
但現在有什麼好?
What good is that now?

973
01:43:39,438 --> 01:43:41,338
顯然你忘記了...
Obviously you've forgotten...

974
01:43:41,540 --> 01:43:42,905
...唐，和...
...Tang and...

975
01:43:43,609 --> 01:43:45,201
...微波爐，還有....
...microwave ovens and....

976
01:43:51,684 --> 01:43:53,242
你的臉看起來很可愛
Your face looks pretty.

977
01:43:58,157 --> 01:43:59,454
我的意思是...
l mean...

978
01:44:00,025 --> 01:44:02,050
...如果沒受傷
...not so bruised.

979
01:44:09,235 --> 01:44:10,463
其實...
Look...

980
01:44:11,103 --> 01:44:12,593
...有些事你應該知道
...there's something you'd better know.

981
01:44:14,440 --> 01:44:16,567
你很快就能發現
You're going to find out soon enough.

982
01:44:17,543 --> 01:44:18,840
我懷孕了
l'm pregnant.

983
01:44:21,647 --> 01:44:23,638
是Michael的孩子
lt's Michael's baby.

984
01:44:24,984 --> 01:44:27,145
但其實你才是真正的父親
You're just the body father.

985
01:44:32,591 --> 01:44:34,456
你怎麼知道是我的...
How do you know it's mine...

986
01:44:36,629 --> 01:44:37,926
...不是Bethlehem的?
...not Bethlehem's?

987
01:44:42,568 --> 01:44:45,230
他每天晚上都和我在一起
He tried with me almost every night.

988
01:44:48,908 --> 01:44:50,569
但是他不行...
He couldn't do it...

989
01:44:54,446 --> 01:44:56,073
...所以他打我
...so he beat me.

990
01:45:00,219 --> 01:45:02,312
還說是我的錯
Said it was my fault.

991
01:45:08,627 --> 01:45:09,594
對不起, Abby
l'm sorry, Abby.

992
01:45:49,335 --> 01:45:50,666
怎麼了?
What is it?

993
01:45:51,737 --> 01:45:53,227
出什麼事了?
What's wrong?

994
01:45:56,141 --> 01:45:57,199
是孩子嗎?
ls it the baby?

995
01:45:58,410 --> 01:45:59,968
那個關口空了
The pass is clear.

996
01:46:22,234 --> 01:46:23,701
發生了什麼事?
What happened?

997
01:46:26,105 --> 01:46:28,130
還好，你把我們的東西搬出來了
Good, you got our stuff out.

998
01:46:28,340 --> 01:46:29,602
當然
Of course.

999
01:46:30,542 --> 01:46:31,668
什麼?
What?

1000
01:46:33,579 --> 01:46:35,069
我不明白
l don't understand.

1001
01:46:36,148 --> 01:46:38,048
火是我放的
l set the fire.

1002
01:46:41,253 --> 01:46:43,346
難道你認為我們要永遠呆在這裡嗎?
Did you think we'd stay here forever?

1003
01:46:43,923 --> 01:46:45,083
當然不是
No.

1004
01:46:48,160 --> 01:46:51,994
如果你能和我一起走 給孩子找一個安全的地方我會很感激的...
l'd appreciate it if you'd walk with me to find someplace safe for the baby...

1005
01:46:52,197 --> 01:46:53,960
...否則我們就分開
...then we can split up.

1006
01:46:54,166 --> 01:46:55,030
你刮臉了
You shaved.

1007
01:46:57,169 --> 01:46:58,101
看起來不錯
Looks nice.

1008
01:47:05,377 --> 01:47:06,969
你真是很奇怪!
You're really weird!

1009
01:47:07,179 --> 01:47:08,510
你知道嗎?
You know that?

1010
01:47:15,821 --> 01:47:17,948
你聽說過Saint Rose嗎, Abby?
You ever heard of Saint Rose, Abby?

1011
01:47:18,524 --> 01:47:20,287
我聽別人說過
l've heard people talk.

1012
01:47:20,492 --> 01:47:22,619
我聽過很多名字...
l've heard lots of names...

1013
01:47:23,228 --> 01:47:25,958
...Bliss, Hesperia, 還有New Eden
...Bliss, Hesperia, and New Eden.

1014
01:47:26,298 --> 01:47:28,892
Sheriff Briscoe 說這是幻想
Sheriff Briscoe says it's a fantasy.

1015
01:47:29,134 --> 01:47:30,396
他錯了
He's wrong.

1016
01:47:30,736 --> 01:47:32,601
Saint Rose 就在那裡...
Saint Rose is out there...

1017
01:47:33,138 --> 01:47:34,366
...我要找到它
...and l'm going to find it.

1018
01:47:34,573 --> 01:47:36,097
但你是郵差
But you're the postman.

1019
01:47:36,308 --> 01:47:37,935
我誰也不是, Abby
l'm nobody, Abby.

1020
01:47:52,992 --> 01:47:54,584
我討厭這樣
This is what l hate.

1021
01:47:54,793 --> 01:47:56,124
陌生人
Strangers.

1022
01:47:56,328 --> 01:47:58,888
你是對她說 嗨, 還是把她攔下來?
Do you say hi, or do you blow their heads off?

1023
01:47:59,098 --> 01:48:01,760
他們到底想分享他們所有的還是奪去你有的?
Do they want to share what they got or take what you have?

1024
01:48:03,202 --> 01:48:06,831
如果他們想要奪取,你怎麼去阻止他們?
lf they want to take, how far are you willing to go to stop them?

1025
01:48:08,007 --> 01:48:09,804
好了, 停在那兒
All right, that's far enough.

1026
01:48:10,943 --> 01:48:12,638
我們不想惹麻煩
We don't want any trouble.

1027
01:48:15,681 --> 01:48:16,978
我也不想,先生
Me neither, mister.

1028
01:48:19,251 --> 01:48:20,081
你是誰?
What are you?

1029
01:48:20,285 --> 01:48:21,843
18號郵遞員...
Carrier 1 8...

1030
01:48:22,321 --> 01:48:24,186
...美國郵政服務
...U.S. Postal Service.

1031
01:48:25,157 --> 01:48:26,021
有信嗎?
Got any mail?

1032
01:48:26,392 --> 01:48:27,984
那不可能
That's impossible.

1033
01:48:30,629 --> 01:48:32,324
你沒聽說過郵差嗎?
Ain't you heard of The Postman?

1034
01:48:33,999 --> 01:48:35,057
沒有
No.

1035
01:48:35,768 --> 01:48:37,065
告訴我們
Tell us.

1036
01:48:37,936 --> 01:48:40,564
他是倖存的最偉大的人
He's only the greatest man who ever lived.

1037
01:48:41,173 --> 01:48:43,038
他穿過荒地...
He crossed the wasteland...

1038
01:48:43,242 --> 01:48:45,301
...用拳頭把敵人打倒...
...shook his fist at the enemy...

1039
01:48:45,511 --> 01:48:49,038
...把口水吐到Bethlehem將軍的眼睛裡
...and spit in the eye of General Bethlehem himself.

1040
01:48:49,782 --> 01:48:52,649
他現在和Starkey總統一起從東邊回來了
He's back east with President Starkey right now.

1041
01:48:53,519 --> 01:48:55,248
誰告訴你這些?
Who told you all this?

1042
01:48:55,821 --> 01:48:58,221
郵局局長Ford Lincoln Mercury
Postmaster Ford Lincoln Mercury.

1043
01:48:58,490 --> 01:49:00,958
他親自參加了重建的國會
He's in direct contact with the restored Congress.

1044
01:49:01,160 --> 01:49:02,957
親自參加?!
Direct contact?!

1045
01:49:03,228 --> 01:49:04,422
我不相信!
l don't believe this!

1046
01:49:04,630 --> 01:49:06,029
郵遞員營地!
Carrier camp!

1047
01:49:06,231 --> 01:49:07,721
郵遞員營地!
Carrier camp!

1048
01:49:07,933 --> 01:49:09,423
大家集合!
Gather around, everybody!

1049
01:49:09,635 --> 01:49:12,229
快,集合 又來了一封信
Come on, gather around. Got another letter here.

1050
01:49:13,605 --> 01:49:15,197
昨晚到的
lt came in last night.

1051
01:49:18,610 --> 01:49:21,977
-這兒怎麼了? -郵差送給Ford又一封信
-What's all this? -The Postman sent Ford another letter.

1052
01:49:22,181 --> 01:49:23,842
他要讀了
He's going to read it.

1053
01:49:25,651 --> 01:49:27,346
你們好，郵遞員們
''Hello, all postal carriers.

1054
01:49:32,191 --> 01:49:35,183
我現在在Minneapolis和Starkey總統在一起...
l'm here in Minneapolis with President Starkey...

1055
01:49:35,394 --> 01:49:37,294
...但我的心跟你們在一起
...but my thoughts are with you.

1056
01:49:37,663 --> 01:49:38,652
請記住...
Remember...

1057
01:49:38,864 --> 01:49:41,697
...沒有什麼值得整晚去做
...nothing worth doing can be done overnight.

1058
01:49:41,900 --> 01:49:45,734
抬起你的頭盡力別被擊中
lKeep your chins up and do your best not to get shot.

1059
01:49:45,938 --> 01:49:46,768
你們是...
Signed...

1060
01:49:47,406 --> 01:49:48,430
...郵差 !
...The Postman'' !

1061
01:49:52,211 --> 01:49:54,702
他的信總是很短
His letters are always kind of short.

1062
01:49:55,814 --> 01:49:57,247
等等! 還有一個附言
Hold on! There's a P.S.

1063
01:49:58,717 --> 01:50:01,413
有人知道附言代表什麼?
Does anybody know what P.S. stands for?

1064
01:50:18,103 --> 01:50:20,401
-天哪! -那是H.S., Eddie
-Holy shit! -That would be H.S., Eddie.

1065
01:50:21,540 --> 01:50:24,600
當我在Pineview生活時我見過他
No, l saw him once when l lived in Pineview.

1066
01:50:24,810 --> 01:50:26,141
它就是郵差
lt's The Postman.

1067
01:50:58,844 --> 01:51:00,744
我猜你會說這個
Guess you want to talk about this.

1068
01:51:11,757 --> 01:51:13,622
我找到他了! 我找到他了!
l found him! l found him!

1069
01:51:19,665 --> 01:51:21,223
Minneapolis?
''Minneapolis?''

1070
01:51:21,733 --> 01:51:24,930
P.S. Ford知道做什麼?
''P.S. Ford knows what to do?''

1071
01:51:26,271 --> 01:51:27,533
這是什麼?
What is this?

1072
01:51:28,006 --> 01:51:30,133
這都是什麼? 這究竟是什麼--
What is all this? What the hell--

1073
01:51:30,309 --> 01:51:31,606
我撒謊了!
l lied!

1074
01:51:31,810 --> 01:51:34,973
我告訴人們你親自和我聯繫了
l told people you were in direct contact with me.

1075
01:51:37,282 --> 01:51:40,581
-為什麼? -因為我不想就這樣結束
-Why? -Because l didn't want it to end.

1076
01:51:43,689 --> 01:51:44,815
看...
Look...

1077
01:51:45,557 --> 01:51:49,220
...我不知道我能呆多久 我是說...
...l don't know how long l can stay. l mean...

1078
01:51:49,428 --> 01:51:50,952
...Starkey總統...
...President Starkey...

1079
01:51:51,163 --> 01:51:55,827
...他一旦傳話給我我又要走
...he's going to send word for me one day and then l'll have to move on.

1080
01:51:56,902 --> 01:51:58,460
你明白嗎?
Do you understand?

1081
01:52:05,644 --> 01:52:08,807
但你一直會呆到他傳話來, 對嗎?
But you'll stay until he sends word, right?

1082
01:52:19,958 --> 01:52:21,482
別這樣 把手放下
Don't do that. Hands down.

1083
01:52:23,295 --> 01:52:26,128
你會一直呆到Starkey總統傳話過來,對嗎?
You're staying till President Starkey sends word, right?

1084
01:52:26,632 --> 01:52:27,656
對!
Yes!

1085
01:52:27,866 --> 01:52:29,766
直到他傳話，沒錯
Until he sends word. Right.

1086
01:52:31,003 --> 01:52:34,336
你能說一些話讓他們知道真的是你?
Could you say a few words just so they know it's really you?

1087
01:52:40,078 --> 01:52:41,409
我就是（郵差）
lt's me.

1088
01:53:00,032 --> 01:53:01,465
下來了
Coming down.

1089
01:53:05,103 --> 01:53:07,435
我們先把所有信件運到這裡
We bring all the mail here first.

1090
01:53:08,173 --> 01:53:09,470
分揀
We sort it.

1091
01:53:09,675 --> 01:53:11,905
編組 再送出去
We group it. Then it goes out.

1092
01:53:12,544 --> 01:53:14,876
到目前為止，我們已經有30條線路了
So far, we got 30 routes.

1093
01:53:25,657 --> 01:53:27,716
你把tyranny寫錯了
You spelled ''tyranny'' wrong.

1094
01:53:29,561 --> 01:53:30,789
天哪!
Boy!

1095
01:53:31,396 --> 01:53:32,954
他太帥了
He's smart.

1096
01:53:34,132 --> 01:53:36,066
快速地完成...
From the swift completion...

1097
01:53:37,135 --> 01:53:38,727
...指定的任務
...of their appointed rounds.

1098
01:53:41,273 --> 01:53:44,606
祝賀大家，你們現在是美國郵遞員了
Congratulations. You are now U.S. postal carriers.

1099
01:53:57,522 --> 01:53:58,784
你多大了?
How old are you?

1100
01:53:59,524 --> 01:54:01,458
我68了,先生
l'm 68, sir.

1101
01:54:04,863 --> 01:54:06,558
我能問你一個問題嗎?
Can l ask you a question?

1102
01:54:09,701 --> 01:54:11,032
你能騎馬嗎?
Can you ride?

1103
01:54:11,269 --> 01:54:12,258
不能
No.

1104
01:54:12,437 --> 01:54:14,268
也不能走太遠
Can't walk too good either.

1105
01:54:15,040 --> 01:54:16,871
那你為什麼要來這裡?
So why are you here?

1106
01:54:17,442 --> 01:54:19,034
我知道材料學
l know stuff.

1107
01:54:24,850 --> 01:54:26,283
你在哪兒刻的?
Where did you get that?

1108
01:54:29,688 --> 01:54:31,918
1970年
1 9 70.

1109
01:54:32,924 --> 01:54:35,358
一個大眼睛女孩兒...
A girl with eyes as big as saucers...

1110
01:54:35,560 --> 01:54:38,120
...在一個叫Saigon的小鎮給我刻的
...did me in a little town called Saigon.

1111
01:54:56,982 --> 01:54:59,576
Ford讓我住他的地方
Ford wants me to have his place.

1112
01:55:00,752 --> 01:55:01,912
他說是最好的
Said it's the best.

1113
01:55:05,957 --> 01:55:07,185
我在另一邊
l'm on the other side.

1114
01:55:10,662 --> 01:55:12,687
我在這兒有很多屋子
l got plenty of room here.

1115
01:55:17,769 --> 01:55:20,397
和制服一樣多
So much for the uniform theory.

1116
01:55:27,679 --> 01:55:29,772
他是在Oregon邊界被抓住的
He was captured on the Oregon border.

1117
01:55:32,083 --> 01:55:33,914
你到底是誰?
Who the hell are you?

1118
01:55:34,119 --> 01:55:35,017
12號郵遞員
Carrier 1 .

1119
01:55:36,521 --> 01:55:38,045
美國郵政服務
United States Postal Service.

1120
01:55:53,371 --> 01:55:56,238
我要隊伍在拂曉之前動身
l want the camp struck at dawn.

1121
01:55:59,110 --> 01:56:00,543
我們將向北行進!
We'll be moving north!

1122
01:56:06,284 --> 01:56:08,684
你把tyranny寫錯了
You spelled ''tyranny'' wrong.

1123
01:56:12,190 --> 01:56:13,885
我希望他們停止喝酒
l wish they'd stop saluting.

1124
01:56:23,435 --> 01:56:24,834
注意安全
Just stay safe.

1125
01:56:26,037 --> 01:56:27,368
記住...
Remember...

1126
01:56:27,973 --> 01:56:29,964
...郵遞員比郵件重要
...the mailman's more important than the mail.

1127
01:56:31,810 --> 01:56:33,505
天哪，他太帥了
Boy, he's smart.

1128
01:56:37,782 --> 01:56:40,979
在我小的時候我經常把帽子朝後
When l was a kid we used to turn our hat around backwards.

1129
01:56:42,454 --> 01:56:44,319
我認為比較酷
Thought it was cool.

1130
01:56:51,496 --> 01:56:53,123
上帝保佑!
Jesus Christ!

1131
01:57:03,074 --> 01:57:04,132
該死!
Damn!

1132
01:58:12,644 --> 01:58:13,611
我錯過了
l missed him.

1133
02:00:03,621 --> 02:00:05,680
這個鎮叫什麼?
What's the name of this town?

1134
02:00:08,126 --> 02:00:09,593
我們從來沒有給它命名
We never named it.

1135
02:00:12,063 --> 02:00:13,724
我宣佈...
l officially declare...

1136
02:00:13,932 --> 02:00:16,127
...10號郵政所...
...Postal Station Number 1 0...

1137
02:00:17,202 --> 02:00:18,669
...在Elvis, Oregon...
...in Elvis, Oregon...

1138
02:00:18,870 --> 02:00:20,531
...正式開業
...open for business.

1139
02:00:23,408 --> 02:00:27,435
從現在開始你們可以把信件送到下面去，好嗎?
From now on you got to get your mail down there, okay?

1140
02:00:28,379 --> 02:00:30,074
這個看來不能用了
This one doesn't work.

1141
02:00:42,093 --> 02:00:43,526
再讀一遍
Read it again.

1142
02:00:44,362 --> 02:00:45,522
你確定?
Are you sure?

1143
02:00:45,730 --> 02:00:46,822
是的
Yes.

1144
02:00:48,500 --> 02:00:51,094
親愛的媽媽：聽到你的消息真是奇跡
''Dearest Mom: What a miracle to hear from you.''

1145
02:00:57,475 --> 02:00:59,466
生活在變好
Stuff is getting better.

1146
02:00:59,978 --> 02:01:02,412
生活每天都在變好
Stuff is getting better every day.

1147
02:01:06,518 --> 02:01:07,712
我不認識你...
l don't know who you are...

1148
02:01:10,455 --> 02:01:12,855
...但我知道我錯怪你了
...but l do know l was wrong about you.

1149
02:01:17,695 --> 02:01:19,788
鎮長，你也有一封信
Got a letter for you too, Sheriff.

1150
02:01:33,244 --> 02:01:35,007
這是我妹妹來的信
lt's from my sister.

1151
02:01:36,514 --> 02:01:37,981
我還以為她死了
Thought she was dead.

1152
02:01:39,784 --> 02:01:41,183
你想錯了
You thought wrong.

1153
02:02:02,307 --> 02:02:04,366
想跳支舞嗎?
Would you like to dance?

1154
02:02:09,547 --> 02:02:11,742
Well, they say that you can never

1155
02:02:14,152 --> 02:02:15,779
Never go back home

1156
02:02:21,492 --> 02:02:23,653
And if you're bound to wander

1157
02:02:26,764 --> 02:02:28,732
You're bound to be alone

1158
02:02:33,605 --> 02:02:35,869
You say I got no right

1159
02:02:37,242 --> 02:02:39,437
To feel what I feel

1160
02:02:40,345 --> 02:02:42,438
When I look into your eyes

1161
02:02:43,982 --> 02:02:45,210
跳個舞好嗎?
Want to dance?

1162
02:02:45,884 --> 02:02:48,216
But that I dream of you

1163
02:02:49,120 --> 02:02:50,815
Most every night

1164
02:02:52,857 --> 02:02:54,848
Comes as no surprise

1165
02:02:58,463 --> 02:03:02,422
Well, I've been Out on this road for so long

1166
02:03:05,203 --> 02:03:06,431
Far and wide

1167
02:03:07,639 --> 02:03:08,901
Do I roam

1168
02:03:11,342 --> 02:03:15,210
But something in your smile tells me

1169
02:03:16,547 --> 02:03:19,209
I'm almost home

1170
02:03:37,835 --> 02:03:39,359
I was lost in the dark

1171
02:03:39,804 --> 02:03:40,896
All alone

1172
02:03:42,707 --> 02:03:44,140
Till the light

1173
02:03:44,342 --> 02:03:46,833
In your eyes showed me

1174
02:03:47,812 --> 02:03:49,177
I was almost

1175
02:03:49,914 --> 02:03:51,939
Home is where the heart is

1176
02:03:53,418 --> 02:03:54,385
And my heart goes with you

1177
02:03:55,586 --> 02:03:57,747
I would travel till the end of time

1178
02:03:58,957 --> 02:04:01,391
If that's what I have to do

1179
02:04:02,126 --> 02:04:04,856
Just to spend one night

1180
02:04:05,263 --> 02:04:07,823
Till your sweet love light

1181
02:04:08,032 --> 02:04:09,431
Come down

1182
02:04:12,136 --> 02:04:14,502
Shining down on me

1183
02:04:28,720 --> 02:04:29,880
喂喂
Hello.

1184
02:04:32,957 --> 02:04:34,720
你在跟誰說話?
Who do you talk to?

1185
02:04:34,993 --> 02:04:37,962
試了7年了什麼都沒有...
Not a soul in 7 years of trying...

1186
02:04:38,229 --> 02:04:39,560
...但是我願意
...but l will.

1187
02:04:43,601 --> 02:04:44,761
來點嗎?
Want some?

1188
02:04:44,969 --> 02:04:46,527
不了，謝謝
No, thanks.

1189
02:04:47,171 --> 02:04:49,537
別讓孩子看見這些
Don't let the kids see that.

1190
02:04:49,874 --> 02:04:51,569
你帶個頭,看看
You go ahead, take a look.

1191
02:04:52,377 --> 02:04:54,845
我是一個航空工程師
l was an aerospace engineer.

1192
02:04:55,213 --> 02:04:58,444
我幫助設計了伽利略號宇宙空間站
l helped design the Galileo Space Station.

1193
02:04:58,850 --> 02:04:59,908
真的?
No shit?

1194
02:05:00,118 --> 02:05:01,312
真的
No shit.

1195
02:05:02,220 --> 02:05:05,314
我曾夢想它繞著地球永遠轉下去...
l dream it's orbiting the Earth forever...

1196
02:05:06,124 --> 02:05:07,785
...裝著一打死人骨頭...
...with a dozen human skeletons...

1197
02:05:08,659 --> 02:05:10,320
...對著別人咧著嘴笑...
...all grinning at each other...

1198
02:05:11,062 --> 02:05:12,893
...嘲笑我們下面這些人
...laughing at us down here.

1199
02:05:24,609 --> 02:05:26,702
-怎麼了? -是Tony
-What is it? -lt's Tony.

1200
02:05:27,211 --> 02:05:28,610
他遲到了
He's overdue.

1201
02:05:30,782 --> 02:05:32,249
那是5號
That makes 5.

1202
02:05:33,317 --> 02:05:35,251
所有南方的路線
All on southern routes.

1203
02:05:41,692 --> 02:05:43,455
還是孩子
Just children.

1204
02:05:44,095 --> 02:05:45,960
你給我的都是孩子
You bring me children.

1205
02:05:46,397 --> 02:05:48,092
我要一個男人
l want a man.

1206
02:05:52,804 --> 02:05:54,567
我們知道出生和...
We got births and...

1207
02:05:54,772 --> 02:05:55,898
...死亡
...deaths.

1208
02:05:56,107 --> 02:05:58,575
知道天氣 大部分談話
Got weather. Mostly gossip.

1209
02:05:58,910 --> 02:06:00,434
這裡什麼都沒有
There's nothing here.

1210
02:06:00,878 --> 02:06:02,175
什麼都沒有?
Nothing?

1211
02:06:03,047 --> 02:06:04,344
所有的...
Everything...

1212
02:06:04,549 --> 02:06:05,880
...都在這
...is here.

1213
02:06:06,884 --> 02:06:10,342
我是唯一看見這些的?!
Am l the only one who sees that?!

1214
02:06:10,755 --> 02:06:11,779
什麼?
What?

1215
02:06:21,499 --> 02:06:24,366
一個軍人,特別是個指揮官...
A military man, especially a commander...

1216
02:06:24,569 --> 02:06:26,002
...應該有一本帳
...should keep a journal.

1217
02:06:26,337 --> 02:06:28,498
在他死後,這是唯一的防禦...
After he's gone, it's the only real defense...

1218
02:06:28,673 --> 02:06:31,665
...對付那些後來出現的誹謗
...against the slander that later arises.

1219
02:06:56,801 --> 02:06:59,031
告訴我你還知道些什麼
Tell me about the other stuff you know.

1220
02:07:53,524 --> 02:07:54,456
糟糕!
Shit!

1221
02:09:39,664 --> 02:09:41,063
把屍體抬走
Get rid of the bodies.

1222
02:09:42,133 --> 02:09:44,931
我不想讓這些人怪我們所做的
l don't want these people blamed for what we did.

1223
02:09:47,371 --> 02:09:50,534
無論大雪還是暴雨 無論是炎炎烈日還是漆黑夜晚...
Neither snow, nor rain, nor gloom of night...

1224
02:09:52,610 --> 02:09:55,272
...穿過強盜的地獄, 穿過戰火...
...through bandit's hell, through firefight...

1225
02:09:57,114 --> 02:09:59,582
...穿過洪水和瘟疫 我們不能失敗...
...through flood and plague we cannot fail...

1226
02:10:01,519 --> 02:10:04,113
...什麼都不能阻止郵件
...no Holnist trash will stop the mail.

1227
02:10:06,791 --> 02:10:09,089
你現在是美國郵遞員
You are now U.S. Postal Carriers.

1228
02:10:11,829 --> 02:10:13,387
他們修改了誓詞
They changed the oath.

1229
02:10:14,065 --> 02:10:15,123
Ford的主意
Ford's idea.

1230
02:10:16,033 --> 02:10:17,261
身份
Figures.

1231
02:10:18,235 --> 02:10:20,703
他們從來沒問過他們要取代誰...
They don't think to ask who they're replacing...

1232
02:10:20,905 --> 02:10:22,065
...或者為什麼
...or why.

1233
02:10:22,973 --> 02:10:24,133
先生?
Sir?

1234
02:10:27,411 --> 02:10:29,777
如果能和您握手我會感到很光榮的
lt'd be an honor if l could shake your hand.

1235
02:10:31,982 --> 02:10:32,641
我認識你嗎?
Do l know you?

1236
02:10:35,653 --> 02:10:37,120
我想不認識
l don't think so.

1237
02:10:39,957 --> 02:10:41,015
好運
Good luck, then.

1238
02:10:50,868 --> 02:10:52,165
好孩子
Nice kid.

1239
02:10:52,937 --> 02:10:54,996
要不了多久你就沒命了
He'll probably be dead in a week.

1240
02:10:55,206 --> 02:10:57,367
現在不是你的錯
Now that is not your fault.

1241
02:10:57,775 --> 02:11:01,176
你已經精疲力盡了，你需要休息 那裡有食物--
You're exhausted. You need rest. There's food--

1242
02:11:03,080 --> 02:11:04,980
-你去哪兒? -22號路線
-Where are you going? -Route .

1243
02:11:05,549 --> 02:11:07,813
你下來 下馬
You're grounded. Get off the horse.

1244
02:11:08,786 --> 02:11:09,616
你知道規則的
You know the rule.

1245
02:11:09,987 --> 02:11:10,783
什麼規則?
What rule?

1246
02:11:12,189 --> 02:11:14,384
22號太靠近南邊了 下馬
, it's too far south. Get off the horse.

1247
02:11:14,592 --> 02:11:15,991
但是他們在等著--
But they're waiting on--

1248
02:11:16,193 --> 02:11:17,820
你快給我下馬！
Get off the goddamn horse!

1249
02:11:20,264 --> 02:11:22,129
我回來處理的
l'll tie him off to this one.

1250
02:11:22,533 --> 02:11:24,000
你不能再這麼做了
You can't keep doing this!

1251
02:11:24,935 --> 02:11:26,630
-做什麼？ -跑所有的線路
-Doing what? -Riding all the routes.

1252
02:11:26,837 --> 02:11:28,737
你這樣救不了任何人
You're not saving anybody.

1253
02:11:30,674 --> 02:11:33,700
我有沒有告訴你我怎樣成為一個郵差的？
Did l ever tell you how l got to be a postman?

1254
02:11:35,579 --> 02:11:37,342
我不知道你是哭還是笑
l don't know if you'd laugh or cry.

1255
02:11:42,820 --> 02:11:43,912
那是什麼？
What is it?

1256
02:11:45,756 --> 02:11:46,586
當心！
Watch out!

1257
02:11:54,365 --> 02:11:55,855
著火了，快跑
We got fire! Move!

1258
02:12:31,469 --> 02:12:34,131
-郵資欠費 -Elvis巡邏
-''Postage due.'' -Elvis patrol.

1259
02:12:39,543 --> 02:12:41,238
你想要挑起戰爭嗎？
You want a war?

1260
02:12:42,880 --> 02:12:44,905
你想要挑起戰爭嗎？！
You want a war?!

1261
02:12:45,516 --> 02:12:47,177
我就跟你來場...
l'll give you...

1262
02:12:47,384 --> 02:12:49,181
硬仗！
...a war!

1263
02:12:50,020 --> 02:12:51,419
我就是為戰爭
l was...

1264
02:12:51,622 --> 02:12:54,056
而生！
...born for it!

1265
02:12:54,992 --> 02:12:56,619
兇手！
You murderers!

1266
02:12:59,230 --> 02:13:00,993
你以為你可以騎馬？
You think you can ride?!

1267
02:13:02,533 --> 02:13:04,865
那今天就是你的幸運日
Then today's your lucky day!

1268
02:13:05,636 --> 02:13:07,228
Bethlehem說...
Bethlehem says...

1269
02:13:08,072 --> 02:13:09,596
他會向北進攻
...he's headed north.

1270
02:13:10,908 --> 02:13:13,274
他將在每個鎮子殺死10個人...
He's going to kill 1 0 people in every town...

1271
02:13:13,477 --> 02:13:15,945
再在地上焚燒他們屍體 以此來報復你
...then burn it to the ground for what you did.

1272
02:13:17,681 --> 02:13:19,911
他說他會到Pineview去
He said that Pineview's on his way.

1273
02:13:21,485 --> 02:13:23,578
他將會在那裡等你 但不會等太久
He'd wait there for you, but not for long.

1274
02:13:25,823 --> 02:13:27,688
我很害怕
l was so scared, sir.

1275
02:13:28,025 --> 02:13:30,391
我以為他們會殺了我
l thought they were going to kill me too.

1276
02:13:37,701 --> 02:13:38,565
看見沒？
See?

1277
02:13:38,769 --> 02:13:40,930
我早告訴過你，我們來得太晚了
We're too late. l told you.

1278
02:13:41,338 --> 02:13:42,703
你打算怎麼辦？
What're you going to do?

1279
02:13:42,907 --> 02:13:44,431
我要阻止他們
l'm going to stop this.

1280
02:13:45,175 --> 02:13:45,971
你不能
You can't.

1281
02:13:46,277 --> 02:13:48,336
你給我讓開，都給我讓開
Get out of the way, Ford. All of you!

1282
02:13:48,546 --> 02:13:49,774
他們會殺了你的
They'll kill you!

1283
02:13:53,751 --> 02:13:54,809
攔住他
Hold him!

1284
02:13:58,088 --> 02:13:58,952
住手
Stop it!

1285
02:14:00,624 --> 02:14:01,716
-你們傷著他了 -沒有
-You're hurting him! -l'm not!

1286
02:14:01,926 --> 02:14:02,893
傷著了
Yes, you are!

1287
02:14:03,093 --> 02:14:05,425
沒有，我們沒傷害他
l'm not! l'm not hurting him.

1288
02:14:06,363 --> 02:14:10,265
這都是因為我 我沒有執行你的命令
This is all my doing. l went against your orders.

1289
02:14:11,068 --> 02:14:14,834
你叫我埋了那些死屍 但我把他們送到Bethlehem那裡了
You told me to bury the dead Holnists, but l sent them Bethlehem.

1290
02:14:15,039 --> 02:14:16,063
為什麼？
Why?

1291
02:14:16,407 --> 02:14:17,704
我們得讓Bethlehem知道 我們永不放棄
Bethlehem has to know we won't stop!

1292
02:14:18,142 --> 02:14:19,905
真是該死
Goddamn it, Ford!

1293
02:14:21,378 --> 02:14:23,846
那些人是因我們而死啊
Those people are dying because of us!

1294
02:14:24,048 --> 02:14:26,346
他們因為我們所做的才死的阿
They're dying because of what we did.

1295
02:14:26,550 --> 02:14:29,075
不是的 他們是因為Bethlehem才死的
They're not! They're dying because of Bethlehem...

1296
02:14:29,286 --> 02:14:32,380
因為這是個狗屎世界 如果我們要想改變它
...because this is a shitty world! lf we're going to change it...

1297
02:14:32,590 --> 02:14:34,251
就總會有人要犧牲
...then someone might have to die.

1298
02:14:34,458 --> 02:14:37,222
如果我可以替他們在下面受死 我願意，但我做不到
lf l could make it be me down there, l would, but l can't!

1299
02:14:40,631 --> 02:14:41,996
不要啊，求你們了
No! Please!

1300
02:14:44,435 --> 02:14:45,868
-你，滾開 -攔住她
-You, out here! -Hold her!

1301
02:14:46,070 --> 02:14:47,435
求求你了
Please!

1302
02:15:04,521 --> 02:15:06,489
他就在某個地方
He's out there somewhere.

1303
02:15:08,258 --> 02:15:09,486
看著我們
Watching.

1304
02:15:11,929 --> 02:15:13,726
我能感覺得到
l can feel it.

1305
02:15:17,101 --> 02:15:18,932
你也感覺到了，不是嗎？
You feel it too, don't you?

1306
02:15:20,537 --> 02:15:22,869
鎮長，本來大可不必如此
lt didn't have to end like this, Sheriff!

1307
02:15:23,374 --> 02:15:27,174
他知道我在哪裡 如果他是個男人他就會現身
He knew where l'd be if he wanted to face me like a man!

1308
02:15:27,945 --> 02:15:29,537
但他卻像個兔子一樣
lnstead he's hiding...

1309
02:15:29,747 --> 02:15:31,112
躲起來了
...like a rabbit!

1310
02:15:31,582 --> 02:15:33,573
你們的郵差也不過如此
So much for your Postman!

1311
02:15:34,385 --> 02:15:35,647
中尉！
Lieutenant!

1312
02:15:36,553 --> 02:15:37,485
有!
Ready!

1313
02:15:38,922 --> 02:15:40,480
我們甚至不知道他們的名字
We don't even know their names.

1314
02:15:41,692 --> 02:15:43,387
我知道
We know their names.

1315
02:15:48,565 --> 02:15:49,554
那個就是我父親
l think that's my dad.

1316
02:15:58,842 --> 02:15:59,968
瞄準！
Aim!

1317
02:16:00,811 --> 02:16:02,108
繼續前進阿，郵差！
Ride, Postman!

1318
02:16:02,713 --> 02:16:04,010
繼續前進！
Ride!

1319
02:16:04,415 --> 02:16:05,609
你聽見了嗎？!
You hear me?!

1320
02:16:05,816 --> 02:16:07,681
我叫你們繼續前進！
l said, ''Ride!''

1321
02:16:09,186 --> 02:16:09,982
射擊！
Fire!

1322
02:16:33,744 --> 02:16:35,837
天哪，我都幹了些什麼啊！
My God, what have l done?

1323
02:16:38,882 --> 02:16:40,543
Ford所做的是錯的
What Ford did was wrong!

1324
02:16:44,421 --> 02:16:46,514
但我們卻沒有採取任何的措施
But it doesn't change anything...

1325
02:16:46,724 --> 02:16:49,955
來進行補救，不是嗎？
...for any of us, does it?

1326
02:17:12,783 --> 02:17:14,011
人都在這了？
ls this everybody?

1327
02:17:15,119 --> 02:17:16,552
其餘的還在趕路
The rest are on the overdue list.

1328
02:17:18,055 --> 02:17:19,613
那就是都在這了
Then this is everybody.

1329
02:17:20,824 --> 02:17:22,951
有封來自總統的信
Got a letter from the President.

1330
02:17:25,395 --> 02:17:27,022
你們好，郵遞員們！
''Greetings, all carriers.''

1331
02:17:27,231 --> 02:17:28,892
總統好！
Greetings, President Starkey!

1332
02:17:33,170 --> 02:17:35,638
我一直都在和郵差保持聯絡
''l've been in contact with The Postman.

1333
02:17:35,873 --> 02:17:37,670
我收到了所有的報告
And l've received all the reports.

1334
02:17:38,242 --> 02:17:39,903
我為你們自豪
l'm proud of you all.

1335
02:17:40,878 --> 02:17:42,903
在暗無天日的日子裡 在這個黑暗的世界裡
ln dark days, in a weary world...

1336
02:17:43,113 --> 02:17:45,581
你們付出了所有，卻一無所求
...you gave everything and asked for nothing.

1337
02:17:46,650 --> 02:17:49,175
你們打退絕望，重拾希望
You beat back despair and replaced it with hope.

1338
02:17:49,953 --> 02:17:52,319
而你的國家卻無法給你們任何回報
For that, your country can never repay you.

1339
02:17:53,223 --> 02:17:54,747
但是付出的代價太大
But the price is too high...

1340
02:17:56,493 --> 02:17:59,656
而我也不想再看到我的勇士們有任何的犧牲
...and l won't see any more of my bravest die.

1341
02:18:01,231 --> 02:18:03,791
職責所在，我將要解散...
lt is my duty to hereby disband...

1342
02:18:04,001 --> 02:18:07,437
重建的美國的郵政服務
...the Postal Service of the Restored United States.

1343
02:18:08,305 --> 02:18:10,398
請將你們的制服都燒掉...
You are to burn your uniforms...

1344
02:18:10,607 --> 02:18:14,099
而郵差也將立即返回Minneapolis
...and The Postman is to return to Minneapolis at once.

1345
02:18:14,912 --> 02:18:16,311
謝謝
Thank you.

1346
02:18:16,947 --> 02:18:18,574
上帝保佑你們
And God bless you all.

1347
02:18:19,516 --> 02:18:20,710
總統敬上
The President.''

1348
02:18:38,435 --> 02:18:40,665
總統從沒寫過這樣的信
The President never wrote that letter.

1349
02:18:41,205 --> 02:18:43,469
如果他能寫信的話 他就會這麼寫的
lf he could've, that's what he would have said.

1350
02:18:43,774 --> 02:18:45,537
還有一封信是給誰的？
Who's the other letter to?

1351
02:18:45,742 --> 02:18:46,970
Bethlehem.
Bethlehem.

1352
02:18:47,477 --> 02:18:49,877
-我早上就把信送過去 -信上說什麼？
-l'm taking it to him in the morning. -What's it say?

1353
02:18:50,447 --> 02:18:53,382
-內容保密，你知道這是規矩 -信上到底怎麼說的？
-Mail's private, you know that. -What does it say?

1354
02:18:54,852 --> 02:18:56,581
信上說要結束了
lt says it's over.

1355
02:18:56,954 --> 02:18:58,683
就是說我們要放棄了
lt says we quit.

1356
02:18:59,857 --> 02:19:01,757
那是你放棄了
lt says you quit!

1357
02:19:02,392 --> 02:19:03,484
誓詞是怎麼說的？
What about the oath?

1358
02:19:03,694 --> 02:19:05,423
那你告訴我
Tell me something, Ford.

1359
02:19:05,629 --> 02:19:08,621
一個死了的郵遞員又能投遞幾封信呢
How much mail can a dead postman deliver?

1360
02:19:09,833 --> 02:19:11,164
都結束了
lt's over.

1361
02:19:16,139 --> 02:19:17,401
那讓我去送信
Then l'll take it.

1362
02:19:17,975 --> 02:19:19,374
我信不過你
l can't trust you.

1363
02:19:27,484 --> 02:19:29,213
如果這就是結局...
lf this is the end...

1364
02:19:30,954 --> 02:19:34,014
如果這是最後一封投遞的信
...if this is the last piece of mail that ever gets delivered...

1365
02:19:36,627 --> 02:19:38,094
就讓我來發吧
...l'll take it.

1366
02:19:40,063 --> 02:19:43,328
無論誰發這封信，都有可能會犧牲
Whoever delivers this letter, Ford, probably dies for it.

1367
02:19:43,767 --> 02:19:45,894
我仍然還是個郵差！
l'm still a postman!

1368
02:19:49,373 --> 02:19:50,237
你欠我的
You owe it to me.

1369
02:19:52,242 --> 02:19:53,072
我也欠我自己的
l owe it to me.

1370
02:20:08,926 --> 02:20:10,655
那不能怪Ford
It's not Ford's fault.

1371
02:20:11,194 --> 02:20:14,960
他和你不一樣，他沒有你的那些經歷 他們都沒有
He's not like you. He doesn't have your memories. None of them do.

1372
02:20:16,166 --> 02:20:17,793
這就是他們的全部了
This is all they have.

1373
02:20:18,669 --> 02:20:21,103
-這是他們知道的唯一神聖的事 -什麼？
-lt's the only decent thing they know. -What?

1374
02:20:21,305 --> 02:20:22,704
做個郵差！
Being a postman?

1375
02:20:24,241 --> 02:20:26,038
都是胡扯，Abby
lt's all bullshit, Abby.

1376
02:20:26,243 --> 02:20:27,403
全是胡扯
All of it.

1377
02:20:28,278 --> 02:20:31,213
我穿制服只是為了保暖
l took the uniform off a skeleton to stay warm.

1378
02:20:31,581 --> 02:20:34,414
我只是安慰他們而已
l made up the rest to stay fed.

1379
02:20:35,018 --> 02:20:36,178
根本沒有所謂的...
There is no...

1380
02:20:36,386 --> 02:20:38,980
重建的美國
...Restored United States.

1381
02:20:39,923 --> 02:20:41,652
我覺得事情就是如此
l figured it was something like that.

1382
02:20:41,858 --> 02:20:43,826
我要去Saint Rose
l'm going to Saint Rose.

1383
02:20:44,027 --> 02:20:45,858
我帶你一起去
l'm taking you with me.

1384
02:20:46,697 --> 02:20:48,562
我已經幫你把馬準備好了
l've already packed your horse.

1385
02:20:49,466 --> 02:20:51,593
我知道你不想聽
l know you don't want to hear it...

1386
02:20:52,369 --> 02:20:54,667
但是你的腹中有我的孩子
...but that's my child inside you.

1387
02:20:55,539 --> 02:20:57,564
我想讓他出生在一個安全的地方
l want to see it born somewhere safe.

1388
02:21:21,164 --> 02:21:22,995
我想我認出你來了
l thought l recognized you.

1389
02:21:23,900 --> 02:21:26,994
Bethlehem將軍說當我把槍指著你時 你應該跪倒在地
General Bethlehem said you should be on your knees when l do this.

1390
02:21:27,437 --> 02:21:29,337
我才不理那個混蛋說些什麼
l don't give a damn what that asshole said.

1391
02:21:30,474 --> 02:21:32,169
將軍是個了不起的人物
The general is a great man!

1392
02:21:36,747 --> 02:21:38,977
將軍就他媽的是個瘋子
The general is a fucking lunatic.

1393
02:21:44,354 --> 02:21:45,912
你想見識一下什麼是男子漢？
You want to see a man?

1394
02:21:46,957 --> 02:21:48,356
那就是
That's a man.

1395
02:21:52,529 --> 02:21:53,621
準備好沒？
You ready?

1396
02:21:57,968 --> 02:21:59,128
好了
Yes.

1397
02:22:02,739 --> 02:22:05,037
你至少要比Bethlehem強些
You're a better man than Bethlehem.

1398
02:22:06,109 --> 02:22:07,406
我看得出來
l've seen it.

1399
02:22:12,449 --> 02:22:13,541
尊敬的Bethlehem
''To Bethlehem.

1400
02:22:14,518 --> 02:22:16,486
這是我的真心話
This letter is my testimony...

1401
02:22:17,120 --> 02:22:19,520
事實上並沒有
...to the fact that there is no...

1402
02:22:19,723 --> 02:22:21,884
重建後的美國
...Restored United States...

1403
02:22:22,192 --> 02:22:24,387
也沒有什麼郵政服務
...and there is no postal service.''

1404
02:22:26,029 --> 02:22:27,496
他想讓我相信這個？
He expects me to believe this?

1405
02:22:27,831 --> 02:22:28,627
這是真的
lt's true.

1406
02:22:33,136 --> 02:22:35,331
我當時就在那 他解散了郵遞員組織
l was there. He disbanded the carriers...

1407
02:22:36,640 --> 02:22:38,073
然後向西邊走了
...and rode west.

1408
02:22:38,341 --> 02:22:39,205
叛徒！
Traitor!

1409
02:22:42,145 --> 02:22:43,134
這麼說我贏了
Then l've won.

1410
02:22:50,053 --> 02:22:52,487
把我們昨天抓到的那個人帶過來 把他們一起處死
Bring the one we found yesterday. They can die together.

1411
02:22:53,757 --> 02:22:55,088
叛徒！ 你這個叛徒！
You traitor! You're a traitor!

1412
02:23:02,299 --> 02:23:04,358
那個人是那邊的二號人物
That one's the second-in-command.

1413
02:23:04,568 --> 02:23:06,763
怎麼沒讓我感到驚喜呢？
Why doesn't that surprise me?

1414
02:23:10,273 --> 02:23:11,763
我在想，長官...
l was thinking, sir...

1415
02:23:13,343 --> 02:23:16,335
對我們來說把他關起來也許更有價值
...he might be more valuable to us as a prisoner.

1416
02:23:17,581 --> 02:23:19,640
本打算讓你幹掉他的
You were supposed to kill him...

1417
02:23:19,850 --> 02:23:20,976
對嗎？
...weren't you?

1418
02:23:22,385 --> 02:23:24,216
但是我沒辦法靠近他
l couldn't get close enough.

1419
02:23:45,408 --> 02:23:46,500
你是誰？
Who are you?

1420
02:23:47,544 --> 02:23:49,171
我叫Clark
My name's Clark.

1421
02:23:49,379 --> 02:23:52,212
重建後的加州郵遞員
Postal Carrier for the Restored Republic of California.

1422
02:23:52,816 --> 02:23:53,874
你又是誰？
Who are you?

1423
02:24:00,090 --> 02:24:02,615
郵局局長，Ford
Postmaster Ford Lincoln Mercury.

1424
02:24:11,268 --> 02:24:12,530
萬分榮幸！
lt's an honor.

1425
02:24:16,106 --> 02:24:16,970
等一等
Wait!

1426
02:24:19,176 --> 02:24:21,303
等一等，先別開火
Wait a minute. Hold your fire.

1427
02:24:26,416 --> 02:24:27,940
你們倆並不認識？
You two don't know each other?

1428
02:24:36,293 --> 02:24:38,488
這將不會結束
This'll never be over.

1429
02:24:39,095 --> 02:24:40,585
會一直持續下去
lt'll go on.

1430
02:24:42,165 --> 02:24:44,690
除非我是在和一個該死的鬼魂在戰鬥
Except l'll be fighting a goddamn ghost.

1431
02:24:45,669 --> 02:24:48,229
-可以開槍了嗎？ -別開槍，該死的
-Should we fire, sir? -No, goddamn it!

1432
02:24:49,706 --> 02:24:51,435
我不會和鬼魂打仗
l won't fight a ghost.

1433
02:24:53,977 --> 02:24:55,308
Tabula...
Tabula...

1434
02:24:55,979 --> 02:24:57,276
...rasa...
...rasa...

1435
02:24:57,480 --> 02:24:58,742
...先生們
...gentlemen.

1436
02:24:59,716 --> 02:25:01,616
一段清白的歷史
A clean slate.

1437
02:25:02,552 --> 02:25:05,544
我要對所有的郵遞員窮追猛打
l want all mail carriers hunted down.

1438
02:25:06,389 --> 02:25:08,823
我一定要找到那個郵差
l want The Postman found.

1439
02:25:09,025 --> 02:25:10,959
我要狠狠地打擊他
l want him dealt with.

1440
02:25:11,861 --> 02:25:13,556
上校，集合部隊
Colonel, organize the scouts.

1441
02:25:15,365 --> 02:25:16,559
你說他往西走了？
You said he rode west?

1442
02:25:22,038 --> 02:25:23,903
而這是他的二號人物？
And this is his second-in-command?

1443
02:25:27,978 --> 02:25:29,138
是的，長官
Yes, sir!

1444
02:25:42,425 --> 02:25:45,690
我會留你一條命用來談判 要讓郵差投鼠忌器
l'll keep you to bargain with. The Postman is weak that way.

1445
02:26:36,279 --> 02:26:38,213
把槍扔到地上
Set your rifle on the ground!

1446
02:26:38,982 --> 02:26:40,882
扔到地上
Set it on the ground.

1447
02:26:42,485 --> 02:26:44,612
什麼？這個破玩意？
What? This old thing?

1448
02:26:46,256 --> 02:26:47,382
子彈都沒上上去呢
lt isn't even loaded.

1449
02:26:48,725 --> 02:26:50,215
我們這是在哪裡？
Where are we?

1450
02:26:51,294 --> 02:26:53,262
你們在大橋城
You're in Bridge City...

1451
02:26:55,198 --> 02:26:57,223
而這裡不允許槍支
...where we don't allow guns.

1452
02:27:07,777 --> 02:27:09,506
崗哨說你要來了
The sentry said you were coming.

1453
02:27:17,554 --> 02:27:19,488
我知道你，你...
l know you. You're...

1454
02:27:20,056 --> 02:27:20,852
...很出名
...famous.

1455
02:27:22,625 --> 02:27:24,058
曾經是...
l was once...

1456
02:27:24,260 --> 02:27:25,522
...有那麼...
...sort of...

1457
02:27:25,729 --> 02:27:26,991
一點點
...kind of.

1458
02:27:27,297 --> 02:27:28,696
不再是了
Not anymore.

1459
02:27:29,632 --> 02:27:30,428
你們要穿過去？
Looking to cross?

1460
02:27:31,334 --> 02:27:32,562
是的
We will be.

1461
02:27:33,503 --> 02:27:36,438
但現在我們想要一些吃的
Right now we'd appreciate some food.

1462
02:27:38,208 --> 02:27:39,505
沒問題
Okay.

1463
02:27:40,443 --> 02:27:41,910
在我們後面，還有幾個孩子
There are some kids behind us.

1464
02:27:42,112 --> 02:27:43,079
幾個？
How many?

1465
02:27:43,279 --> 02:27:44,109
3個
3.

1466
02:27:45,014 --> 02:27:46,845
3個，好吧
3. Okay.

1467
02:27:49,886 --> 02:27:51,547
進來吧，孩子們
Come on in, guys!

1468
02:27:53,923 --> 02:27:55,982
我知道你們就在那
l know you're out there.

1469
02:29:07,831 --> 02:29:10,061
-等等，等一等 -他想要什麼？
-Wait. Just wait. -What did he want?

1470
02:29:11,835 --> 02:29:13,632
請安靜，他說...
Hold on. He says...

1471
02:29:13,837 --> 02:29:16,032
...他在尋找郵差
...he's looking for The Postman.

1472
02:29:16,573 --> 02:29:18,598
再沒有這樣一回事了
There's no such thing anymore.

1473
02:29:22,312 --> 02:29:25,145
但那個騎馬的人說有這麼一回事
The man on the horse says there is.

1474
02:29:25,682 --> 02:29:27,513
他認為郵差就在這裡
He thinks he's here.

1475
02:29:27,951 --> 02:29:30,078
而他會帶著他的同夥再回來
And he's coming back with friends.

1476
02:29:35,492 --> 02:29:37,426
郵差時幹嗎的？
What's a postman?

1477
02:29:55,278 --> 02:29:56,643
你從來沒聽說過郵差？
You never heard of a postman?

1478
02:30:34,317 --> 02:30:35,443
你就是那個郵差？
Are you The Postman?

1479
02:30:41,224 --> 02:30:42,248
對
Yeah.

1480
02:30:43,726 --> 02:30:45,455
夥計，我聽說過你啊
l heard of you, man.

1481
02:30:46,362 --> 02:30:47,795
你很出名
You're famous.

1482
02:30:49,766 --> 02:30:51,495
也許，是吧
Yeah, l guess l am.

1483
02:30:53,202 --> 02:30:54,931
但突然之間 我已經...
And all of a sudden, l'm not...

1484
02:30:55,438 --> 02:30:57,406
...不再是個郵差了
...wearing the right clothes.

1485
02:31:11,921 --> 02:31:14,185
夥計，你會喜歡上這玩意的
Man, you're going to love this!

1486
02:31:14,591 --> 02:31:17,287
打開第二道瀑布
Open that second chute, bro!

1487
02:31:33,910 --> 02:31:36,174
郵差先生，你很有天賦
You have a gift, Postman.

1488
02:31:37,780 --> 02:31:40,180
在Pineview，我看見它又回來了
l saw it back in Pineview.

1489
02:31:42,652 --> 02:31:45,519
你給了我們都已經遺忘了的寶貴財富
You've given us all back what we'd forgotten.

1490
02:31:47,423 --> 02:31:50,449
你讓March覺得她彷彿重見光明
You made Mrs. March feel like she could see again.

1491
02:31:52,195 --> 02:31:55,790
你讓Ford覺得他就是這個世界的一分子
You made Ford feel like he was part of the world.

1492
02:31:58,735 --> 02:32:01,169
你給了我們希望...
You give out hope like it was...

1493
02:32:01,371 --> 02:32:03,339
...就像點亮你口袋裡的蠟燭
...candy in your pocket.

1494
02:32:19,455 --> 02:32:20,820
你還記得這個嗎？
Remember this?

1495
02:32:22,558 --> 02:32:23,957
我記得
l remember.

1496
02:32:25,561 --> 02:32:28,428
我常想，你是故意把這個留給我的
l always like to think that you left it on purpose.

1497
02:32:34,103 --> 02:32:36,128
這對我來說很不容易
This is hard for me.

1498
02:32:40,576 --> 02:32:43,670
Michael是我見過的最好的男人
Michael was the best man l ever knew.

1499
02:32:46,382 --> 02:32:49,977
我從來沒想過 我會像愛他那樣去愛另外一個人
l never thought there'd be another man l could love the way l loved him.

1500
02:32:53,856 --> 02:32:56,518
我沒法看得那麼遠
l couldn't see it for so long.

1501
02:32:59,162 --> 02:33:00,993
而你現在就要離開
And now you're leaving.

1502
02:33:05,501 --> 02:33:06,627
我害怕
And l'm afraid.

1503
02:33:10,206 --> 02:33:12,766
我害怕你再也找不到你的Saint Rose
l'm afraid you'll never find your Saint Rose.

1504
02:33:13,543 --> 02:33:14,407
這不重要
lt's not important.

1505
02:33:14,610 --> 02:33:17,340
我害怕你再也看不到你的小孩
l'm afraid you'll never see your baby.

1506
02:33:45,575 --> 02:33:49,409
我需要充足的電源！ 這個傢伙要走很遠的路呢！
l need full power, man! This dude's got a long way to go!

1507
02:33:54,317 --> 02:33:56,376
這機器運轉得真他媽的完美
This thing's working perfect, man!

1508
02:34:08,331 --> 02:34:10,356
比看起來還要高很多，不是嗎？
A lot higher than it looks, huh?

1509
02:34:20,409 --> 02:34:21,842
你差點就報銷了
You nearly went.

1510
02:34:24,680 --> 02:34:25,339
快進來吧
Get in.

1511
02:34:27,016 --> 02:34:29,644
在前面有三個規模很大的鎮子
There's 3 good-sized towns up ahead...

1512
02:34:29,852 --> 02:34:33,447
如果你能說服他們跟你走 你就能找到足夠的幫手
...with enough people to help you if you can convince them to come.

1513
02:34:36,993 --> 02:34:38,756
不要告訴任何人
Don't tell anybody...

1514
02:34:38,961 --> 02:34:42,226
說我喜歡玩這玩意，僅僅因為它好玩
...l like to ride this damn thing just for the hell of it.

1515
02:34:42,431 --> 02:34:45,696
你知道，作為一個領導 我得注意自身形象
Being a city official has its perks, you know?

1516
02:34:53,709 --> 02:34:57,440
相信我吧，夥計 這會讓你更快的
Trust me, man. This'll get you there a lot faster.

1517
02:35:03,052 --> 02:35:04,246
我怎麼停下來呢？
How do l stop?

1518
02:35:04,754 --> 02:35:07,018
別再這裡婆婆媽媽了
Quit worrying about the little things.

1519
02:35:07,223 --> 02:35:09,214
祝你好運，跑得飛快！
Good luck, and Godspeed.

1520
02:35:25,408 --> 02:35:27,467
長官，我向您報告！
Reporting for duty, sir!

1521
02:35:27,677 --> 02:35:29,304
-知道該怎麼做嗎？ -去說服人們
-Know what to do? -Talk to the people.

1522
02:35:29,846 --> 02:35:31,211
告訴他們這很重要
Tell them it's important.

1523
02:35:31,414 --> 02:35:32,745
告訴他們我們可以做到
Tell them we can make a difference.

1524
02:35:33,816 --> 02:35:37,308
再向前衝，親愛的朋友們 再向前衝
''Once more unto the breach, dear friends, once more...

1525
02:35:37,520 --> 02:35:39,852
...或者以死守衛我們的城牆
...or close the wall with our dead!

1526
02:35:40,223 --> 02:35:44,250
在和平時期，我們要謙虛彬彬有禮
In peace, nothing so becomes a man as modesty and humility.

1527
02:35:44,460 --> 02:35:47,258
但是一旦爆發戰爭
But when the blast of war blows in our ears...

1528
02:35:47,463 --> 02:35:49,590
我們就要像頭猛虎一樣勇猛
...then imitate the action of the tiger.

1529
02:35:49,799 --> 02:35:54,099
鼓起我們的勇氣 收起我們溫和的本性...
Summon up the blood. Disguise fair nature with rage...

1530
02:35:54,303 --> 02:35:57,466
去和敵人拚個你死我活
...and lend the eye a terrible aspect. ''

1531
02:36:40,950 --> 02:36:42,440
-他們是誰？ -不知道
-Who are they? -l don't know.

1532
02:36:42,652 --> 02:36:45,780
在我看來大部分都是老弱病殘
Looks like mostly women and young people to me.

1533
02:36:45,988 --> 02:36:47,114
有多少？
How many?

1534
02:36:47,556 --> 02:36:48,818
那是一支軍隊
lt's an army.

1535
02:36:59,635 --> 02:37:01,125
終於...
At last...

1536
02:37:01,437 --> 02:37:04,998
還是有人鼓起用來和我作戰了
...someone with courage enough to bring the fight to me.

1537
02:37:09,512 --> 02:37:11,002
先生們，算總賬的時候到了
Reckoning, gentlemen!

1538
02:38:04,700 --> 02:38:06,930
他們看起來熱血沸騰
They're an eager-looking bunch!

1539
02:38:34,830 --> 02:38:37,594
士氣真的是很重要
Morale is a dangerous thing.

1540
02:38:39,568 --> 02:38:41,399
把俘虜帶上來
Bring up the prisoner!

1541
02:38:42,038 --> 02:38:43,938
讓我們來告訴他們 遊戲該怎麼來玩
We'll show them how this game is played.

1542
02:39:26,415 --> 02:39:27,712
呆在這
Stay here.

1543
02:39:42,298 --> 02:39:43,322
他在投降？
ls he surrendering?

1544
02:39:43,799 --> 02:39:45,528
該死，我不希望這樣
God, l hope not.

1545
02:40:07,423 --> 02:40:09,050
小小搬運工
My little shipping clerk.

1546
02:40:09,658 --> 02:40:11,489
賣複印機的銷售員
Mr. copy-machine salesman.

1547
02:40:12,761 --> 02:40:14,592
我們倆是一對大騙子
We're both a couple of frauds.

1548
02:40:16,899 --> 02:40:18,161
說的沒錯
So be it.

1549
02:40:19,535 --> 02:40:23,096
但是一個偉人是由另一個偉人來成就的
But great men are made by other great men.

1550
02:40:23,706 --> 02:40:24,968
Rommel成就了Patton
Patton had Rommel.

1551
02:40:25,574 --> 02:40:27,599
Lee成就了Grant
Grant had Lee.

1552
02:40:28,344 --> 02:40:29,311
而你將會成就我的霸業
But l get you.

1553
02:40:30,045 --> 02:40:31,478
你不是將軍
You're no general.

1554
02:40:32,581 --> 02:40:33,980
你甚至也不是一個好的畫家
You're not even a good painter.

1555
02:40:36,452 --> 02:40:38,044
你想要激將我？
Trying to goad me into a fight?

1556
02:40:38,254 --> 02:40:41,951
如果戰爭由發起它的人來結束，就非常完美
lt'd be great if wars were fought just by the assholes who started them.

1557
02:40:43,792 --> 02:40:45,282
我們可以對這場戰爭作個了結
We could settle this right here...

1558
02:40:46,529 --> 02:40:47,791
只有你跟我
...you and me.

1559
02:40:49,798 --> 02:40:51,857
不幸的是，這種方法行不通
Unfortunately, it doesn't work that way.

1560
02:40:52,067 --> 02:40:53,830
但是在你的部隊裡卻可以
But it does in your army.

1561
02:40:54,803 --> 02:40:56,828
我引用八大法律中的...
l invoke Law Seven...

1562
02:40:57,506 --> 02:40:58,598
...第七條
...of the Laws of Eight!

1563
02:41:00,643 --> 02:41:04,602
在部隊裡誰都可以挑戰老大的位子
''Any man may challenge for leadership of the clan!''

1564
02:41:04,813 --> 02:41:05,643
我向你挑戰
l challenge you.

1565
02:41:05,848 --> 02:41:10,148
你不是我們一夥的，你沒有這個權力
You're not a Holnist. You're not a member. You don't have the right.

1566
02:41:10,352 --> 02:41:12,149
我擁有所有的權力
l have every right!

1567
02:41:18,093 --> 02:41:19,458
我引用第七條法律
l invoke Law Seven.

1568
02:41:20,930 --> 02:41:21,828
你去哪...?
Where...?

1569
02:41:45,221 --> 02:41:46,483
我要挑戰...
l challenge...

1570
02:41:46,689 --> 02:41:48,452
...老大的位子
...for leadership of the clan!

1571
02:41:48,657 --> 02:41:50,284
我在哪裡見過你？
Where do l know you from?

1572
02:41:51,093 --> 02:41:52,651
你下令搶劫...
''Cry havoc...

1573
02:41:53,062 --> 02:41:55,155
...然後餵養這些戰爭走狗
...and let slip the dogs of war!''

1574
02:41:56,332 --> 02:41:57,458
你還記得那些嗎？
You remember that?

1575
02:41:59,935 --> 02:42:01,300
莎士比亞
Shakespeare.

1576
02:42:02,071 --> 02:42:04,301
那個不想打仗的人
The one who didn't want to fight.

1577
02:42:04,940 --> 02:42:08,535
那時我就應該設法殺死你 但你看起來太強大
l should have found a way to kill you then, but you seemed so strong.

1578
02:42:10,279 --> 02:42:11,507
第七條法律...
Law Seven...

1579
02:42:12,848 --> 02:42:14,008
...那就是
...it is!

1580
02:42:15,117 --> 02:42:17,051
這場戰爭將在這裡作個了結
This war is settled here!

1581
02:43:44,139 --> 02:43:45,800
我研究過人們
l studied people.

1582
02:43:47,276 --> 02:43:49,210
我知道你的問題在哪
l know your problem.

1583
02:43:49,878 --> 02:43:51,140
你知道...
Do you know...

1584
02:43:51,347 --> 02:43:53,372
為什麼你不能打嗎？
...why you can't fight?

1585
02:43:55,584 --> 02:43:58,815
因為你不知道為何而戰
Because you have nothing to fight for.

1586
02:44:01,523 --> 02:44:03,491
你什麼也不關心
You don't care about anything.

1587
02:44:04,560 --> 02:44:07,222
你什麼也不在乎
You don't value anything.

1588
02:44:07,696 --> 02:44:10,426
你對什麼都不信任
You don't believe in anything!

1589
02:44:10,632 --> 02:44:12,759
而那些卻讓我變得更厲害
And that's what makes me better.

1590
02:44:15,070 --> 02:44:16,469
我信任...
l believe...

1591
02:44:17,206 --> 02:44:19,299
...美國
...in the United States.

1592
02:44:58,947 --> 02:45:01,882
我們本可以不這樣的
lt doesn't have to be this way.

1593
02:45:02,818 --> 02:45:05,048
我們本可以不用互相殘殺
We don't have to kill each other.

1594
02:45:07,423 --> 02:45:08,981
第三條法律...
''Law Three:

1595
02:45:09,625 --> 02:45:10,853
仁慈...
Mercy...

1596
02:45:11,260 --> 02:45:12,750
...是留給弱者的
...is for the weak.''

1597
02:45:12,961 --> 02:45:14,519
Ford，不要
Ford, don't!

1598
02:45:14,797 --> 02:45:16,196
第八條法律
''Law Eight:

1599
02:45:16,598 --> 02:45:18,998
只有一種懲罰...
There's only one penalty...

1600
02:45:19,835 --> 02:45:22,030
...而那就是死
...and that penalty is death.''

1601
02:45:27,843 --> 02:45:29,367
他不值得的
He isn't worth it.

1602
02:45:33,115 --> 02:45:35,140
現在我是部隊的頭兒
l'm the head of the clan now!

1603
02:45:37,352 --> 02:45:39,081
將會產生新的法律
There are going to be new laws!

1604
02:45:40,556 --> 02:45:41,921
第一條：
Law One:

1605
02:45:43,725 --> 02:45:45,192
不再殺戮
No more killing.

1606
02:45:46,094 --> 02:45:48,187
我們將擁有和平
There's going to be peace!

1607
02:46:06,081 --> 02:46:08,072
你覺得這樣如何？
How about it, Ford Lincoln Mercury?

1608
02:46:14,423 --> 02:46:15,754
Ford，要像個領袖的樣子
Be a leader, Ford.

1609
02:46:19,094 --> 02:46:20,561
第八條法律
Law Eight:

1610
02:46:25,534 --> 02:46:26,865
活著...
Live...

1611
02:46:27,069 --> 02:46:28,627
...就好好活
...and let live.

1612
02:47:53,121 --> 02:47:55,021
你爸爸寫信來說
Your daddy wrote to tell you...

1613
02:47:55,223 --> 02:47:57,919
他會盡快趕回來的
...he'll be here as soon as he can...

1614
02:47:58,160 --> 02:48:00,685
他非常愛你
...and that he loves you very much.

1615
02:48:08,637 --> 02:48:10,070
信件太慢了
Mail's slow.

1616
02:48:11,640 --> 02:48:13,631
我打算親自來告訴她
l'm going to have to see about that.

1617
02:48:46,041 --> 02:48:47,531
你的女兒
Your daughter.

1618
02:48:49,711 --> 02:48:51,770
她的名字叫希望
Her name is Hope.

1619
02:49:22,577 --> 02:49:24,841
我父親看到我們是如此的脆弱...
My father saw how fragile we are...

1620
02:49:25,047 --> 02:49:28,483
...如此輕易的就落入暴君的統治
...and how quickly we fell into the hands of tyranny.

1621
02:49:29,451 --> 02:49:31,214
他發現普通人...
He saw that ordinary men...

1622
02:49:31,420 --> 02:49:34,719
...也可以有潛力可挖，可以找到勇氣
...could reach deep within themselves and find courage.

1623
02:49:35,090 --> 02:49:38,753
他發現如果我們作為一個國家來溝通...
He saw that if we began to communicate as a nation...

1624
02:49:38,960 --> 02:49:40,860
...我們就可以再一次強大起來
...we could become strong again...

1625
02:49:41,063 --> 02:49:42,325
團結起來
...united.

1626
02:49:43,065 --> 02:49:45,431
但是他從來沒有真正見到過Saint Rose
But he never did see Saint Rose.

1627
02:49:47,002 --> 02:49:48,333
他說...
He said...

1628
02:49:49,004 --> 02:49:50,995
...還有太多的事情要去做
...there was too much to be done.

1629
02:49:52,641 --> 02:49:54,131
他許下承諾
He'd made a promise.

1630
02:49:54,676 --> 02:49:57,804
他信守承諾 追逐一個又一個的夢想
And in keeping it, he traded one dream for another.

1631
02:49:58,447 --> 02:50:00,005
無怨無悔
With no regrets.

1632
02:50:03,552 --> 02:50:05,952
所以，為了向我的父親表示敬意....
And so, in honor of my father....

1633
02:50:44,793 --> 02:50:46,454
那個小孩是我
That was me.

1634
02:51:14,390 --> 02:51:38,890
「郵差」 -=結束=-
